headline: How Fast Shifting Analyst Views Are Reshaping Fastenal’s Valuation Story
summary: Fastenal’s latest price target update leaves its fair value estimate largely steady at roughly $43.46 per share, even as a slightly higher discount rate nudges the required return up just a bit. With revenue growth assumptions effectively unchanged, the narrative is shifting less around the destination and more around the path the company will take as analysts weigh its durable strengths against softer near term trends.
